 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "intimate-cookbook",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Correcting probabilities\n",
    "\n",
    "Shows how to correct readout errors and transform to true probability distribution."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "dietary-business",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from qiskit import *\n",
    "from qiskit_ibm_runtime.fake_provider import FakeMelbourne\n",
    "from qiskit.visualization import plot_histogram\n",
    "import mthree"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9844c7e2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup experiment"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "natural-hunter",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "backend = FakeMelbourne()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "featured-translator",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 998.443x535.111 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(5)\n",
    "qc.h(2)\n",
    "qc.cx(2,1)\n",
    "qc.cx(1,0)\n",
    "qc.cx(2,3)\n",
    "qc.cx(3,4)\n",
    "qc.measure_all()\n",
    "qc.draw('mpl')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "37f11bb8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Compile and run circuits and perform mitigation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "nominated-dominican",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trans_qc = transpile(qc, backend)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "computational-fabric",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_counts = backend.run(trans_qc, shots=2048).result().get_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "expanded-ability",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mit = mthree.M3Mitigation(backend)\n",
    "mit.cals_from_system(range(qc.num_qubits))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "fitted-median",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "quasi = mit.apply_correction(raw_counts, range(qc.num_qubits))\n",
    "probs = quasi.nearest_probability_distribution()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6f290531",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plot result"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "completed-accommodation",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 24,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_histogram([raw_counts, probs], figsize=(10,4), legend=['Raw', 'M3'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dangerous-entity",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  }
